OK tram
Oct 2023 • Solo
A not very developed network, it circulates only in the Dubai Marina-Palm Jumeirah-Al Sufouk area. The trams are modern, clean, with air conditioning, respect the timetables. The stations are in closed spaces and have air conditioning, so it is easy to wait for the tram.
Less crowded than the metro.
All in all, an ordinary tram.

Edmonton, Canada8,742 contributions
Good and Frequent Tram
Nov 2023 • Couples
We used this tram a few times in Dubai and found it is conveniently placed to get to the sights that the metro does not go to. It has two connections to the Dubai Metro at Jumeirah Lakes and Dubai Marina stations and provides access to The Palm Island monorail. Tickets for Dubai Metro work with the tram but you have to buy a separate ticket for the monorail. The tram was driverless, safe and relatively inexpensive with plenty of standing room every time we took it.
Written November 20, 2023

The link
Mar 2023
A great convenience to the travelling public as it links metro with JBR beach. If you take the red line metro you can drop at Sobha Realty station and interchange to tram, then drop again at Jumeirah Beach Residence 2. That reduces walking distance to the beach and saves you from the scorching heat of the sun. Tram fare is payable using the NOL card.
